The Spaniard, Mario Yela, was arrested shortly after his ex-wife discovered the bodies in his Hout Bay apartment two weeks ago. CAPE TOWN - The father accused of killing his three-year old twins could be sent for psychiatric evaluation following medical observation this week.The Spaniard, Mario Yela, was arrested shortly after his ex-wife discovered the bodies in his Hout Bay apartment two weeks ago.The Wynberg Magistrates Court has on Wednesday heard concerns over his health and emotional state.Defence advocate William Booth says: There were concerns raised about potential suicide, so that s why I believe this has to be carefully monitored. We're hoping to have him accessed by Friday. So I ll be in a position to decide whether or not we re looking at psychiatric observation. The case has been postponed to Tuesday.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)